  "texts": [
    "These findings open up the possibility that enhanced transnational cooperation may be helpful for these countries in becoming better members of the international research community.",
    "Hence, this data should be used by policymakers and institutions intending to advance the cooperation with other countries or develop their country's ranking in the research.Table 5 analyses the top twenty countries and the statistics reveal that 65 Countries have contributed 1484 papers for this compilation.",
    "Looking at the production of research papers, China and India have contributed more papers, but when looking at the impact of their papers, USA and the UK have contributed most papers with high citation indexes.",
    "This data highlights the different approaches to international research: inclusive of some countries where the number of publications is still being used as the performance indicator as compared to others where focus is put on quality research and international collaboration.",
    "Author co-citation analysisCitation Clustering Analysis is useful to the readers by categorizing a large number of documents into groups according to how often the documents are cited together."
